We now turn to Italy—where a zestful, sensuous cuisine is com- plemented perfectly by a profusion of excellent red and white wines. One of the delights of drinking Italian wine is that, although the quality of the wine exported to America has increased dramatically over the past ten years, the prices have remained relatively low.

Sherry-Lehmann’s list of Italian wines is the largest and the best we have ever been able to offer. Many of our customers already know the delights of Italian wine—and we hope to persuade more and more to sample the wonderful drinking—at low, low cost—that these joyous wines provide.
